cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

The paper deals with the problem of background subtraction in video, which is a common task in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The proposed method involves adaptive initialization of parameters and a deterministic update policy, which suggests the use of machine learning techniques and algorithms. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. The method is evaluated over various challenging scenarios, which indicates the use of multimedia techniques, leading to the possibility of cs.MM (Multimedia) being a relevant category. Finally, the paper deals with the problem of change detection, which is a security-related issue, suggesting the possibility of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) being a relevant category.
